This paper involves natural language processing and clustering techniques to analyze a corpus of financial news reports. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). It also involves machine learning techniques such as k-means clustering, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with analyzing large amounts of text data. The paper also involves cybersecurity (cs.CY) as it deals with financial data. Finally, it could also belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it involves analyzing the relationships between different verbs used in financial news reports.
